  "texts": [
    "The plot shows that most publications on TM belong to computer science (12,109), engineering (3,755), and social sciences (3205), on the other hand, subject areas like pharmacology, toxicology, and pharmaceutics (37) veterinary (10), and dentistry (1) produced the lowest number of publications.",
    "In addition, TM publications in the computer science subject area achieved reasonable citation impact based on their total number of publications (12,109), however, it is worth mentioning that the highest citation impact score was achieved by publications in psychology (20.779), business management and accounting (20.273), and neuroscience (18.989) subject areas.",
    "This indicator must be used with care, especially in the small number of publications and when benchmarking the average influence of the publications of entities with distinct disciplinary profiles.",
    "Citations per publication calculate an average value, and these types of calculations are strongly influenced by outlying publications in a small data set (Elsevier 2024).",
    "Figure 4 shows the most prolific countries on TM worldwide."
